[normal]In early 2012 the WLA boroughs agreed to explore the potential for collaboration on the procurement of public health services in the light of the transfer of these services to local government. A det
[normal]ailed analysis of the business case for collaboration and a business proposition for the creation of a public health procurement hub was produced, demonstrating potential efficiency savings. 
