[normal]Collaborative Workshops[bold] (example)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]In June 2013 the WLA ran a procurement workshop
[normal] entitled 
[normal]Listening, Learning and Improving[bold]. 
[normal]This was c
[normal]haired by one of our Chief Executives and peopled with strategic directors, procurement and delivery staff, as well as Legal, IT, HR and other representatives. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Objective;[bold] 
[normal]shar
[normal]ing
[normal] experiences both goo
[normal]d and bad and discuss
[normal]ing
[normal] solutions to problems and how resolutions were achieved
[normal], 
[normal]test
[normal]ing
[normal] whether optimum solutions were found. Or how we could have done better?
[normal] Thus b
[normal]uilding up a network of 
[normal]‘people who can’[bold] 
[normal]within our boroughs - such that they can be 
[normal]called on in the future to help, support and if necessary lead on future procurements
[normal]. 
[normal]People who can[bold] 
[normal]are not necessarily procurement professionals.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We also run regular procurement 
[normal]learning 
[normal]workshop sessions for the WLA and other boroughs to attend. Each 
[normal]Worksop is themed and for each we invite guest speakers to discuss relevant procurement and supply issues.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Topics covered to date have included;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]•[bold]              [bold]Green Deal[bold] / [bold]•[bold]              [bold]Eco[bold] / [bold]Fuel Poverty[bold] [bold]/ [bold]London Living Wage[bold] /[bold] [bold]RE:FIT / RE:NEW[bold]•[bold]              [bold]Social Inclusion / Third Sector [bold]engagement[bold]•[bold]              [bold]SME / [bold]Cross River Partnership[bold] / Involving Local Suppliers[bold]•[bold]              [bold]Collaborative Procurement[bold]•[bold]              [bold]GPS [bold]initiatives - Contingent labour[bold]•[bold]              [bold]Digital Inclusion [bold]/ P[bold]an London roads and highways framework - GLA[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]We have also had in attendance at our workshops re
[normal]presentatives from;
[normal] 
[normal]non WLA b
[normal]oroughs, London Councils, GLA, Central Government Departments, 
[normal]contractors, 
[normal]trade bodies, 
[normal]regional efficiency agencies specialist industry experts.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Within the WLA
[normal] we have created a formal network of boards, network groups, directors, senior staff and operational staff - flowing down from the Chief Executives - who meet every 4 weeks. To ensure ownership of all matters related to procurement and other collaboration.
[normal]See attached chart.
