[normal]In terms of procurement the focus of this activity is the Procurement Board.  Which is the governing body for the WLA head of procurement
[normal]’
[normal]s programme and to which the annual business plan is presented, debated and signed off.
[normal] 
[normal]This Bo
[normal]ard 
[normal]is 
[normal]chaired by the Chief Executive of Hounslow Council and it has wide membership across the WLA group of
[normal]; Head of Legal Services (Brent
[normal]), Director of Finance (Hillingdon), Me
[normal]mbers (from Hounslow and Barnet
[normal]), Treasurer (Kensington and Chelsea), Head of 
[normal]Procurement (Ealing), Director of Environment (Harrow) and the Director of the WLA.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]A
[normal]ll spend 
[normal]categories 
[normal]are represented in the attached diagram
[normal], 
[normal]each hav
[normal]ing
[normal] a board that look
[normal]s
[normal] for collaborat
[normal]iv
[normal]e opportunities
[normal], 
[normal]be that Property, Estates, Children’s 
[normal]/
[normal] Adult
[normal] services, Transport, Environment, Highways, Waste, Parking, Customer Services, etc. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Within the WLA we operate a standardised 
[normal]Benefit Realisation[bold] 
[normal]process. The concept is aimed at making the link between the cost savings and the benefits identified and established in a business case and secured from a procurement competition, to that which Finance Directors within a borough recognise as being delive
[normal]red on the ground. Thus closing the budgeting
[normal] /
[normal] 
[normal]procurement 
[normal]cycle loop where historically there has been little or no correlation between the costs and benefits that 
[normal]are 
[normal]claim
[normal]ed as
[normal] resultant from a procurement activity
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Whilst this requires extra work as 
[normal]it is a planned discipline within the procurement and finance departments of a borough 
[normal]–
[normal] it
[normal] is useful in that it helps
[normal] in bringing credibility and corporate ownership to the savings claims.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The Benefits Realisation process if overseen by a Board made up o
[normal]f the Finance Directors from all of the boroughs, and is  chaired by an independent Treasurer from outside of the immediate WLA group.
